Motor Industry Workshop Association director Vishal Premlall Director busts myths about saving fuel. CAPE TOWN A number of myths have been circulating about saving fuel.The price of fuel recently increased and motorists in South Africa have to fork out 49 cents per litre more on petrol.Vishal Premlall of Motor Industry Workshop Association debunks the myths around saving fuel.Listen to the audio below.(Edited by Shimoney Regter)